{"word":"H6776 - צֶמֶד - tsemed - tseh'-med - Acre","slug":"H6776","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">צֶמֶד</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>tsemed"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>tseh'-med"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Acre"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E6;&#x05DE;&#x05D3; - tsemed</b> - <i>tseh'-med</i><p/>A <i>yoke</i> or <i>team</i> (that is, pair); hence an <i>acre</i> (that is, day&rsquo;s task for a yoke of cattle to plough): - acre, couple, X together, two [asses], yoke (of oxen)."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H6775\">H6775</a>, <a href=\"#/H6781\">H6781</a>"}]}